Rewrite `TunnelDialog.tsx` from a 570-line monolith into a ~180-line orchestrator shell that owns the state machine, data fetching, handler functions, and an `AnimatePresence` view router delegating to sub-components. The shell renders the `ResponsiveDialog` container, header with status dot, and routes the body content to the active view component.

## File to Modify

`apps/client/src/layers/features/settings/ui/TunnelDialog.tsx`

## New Type and Function

```typescript
type ViewState = 'landing' | 'setup' | 'ready' | 'connecting' | 'connected' | 'error';

function deriveViewState(
  tunnelConfig: TunnelConfig | undefined,
  tunnelState: TunnelState,
  showSetup: boolean
): ViewState {
  if (!tunnelConfig?.tokenConfigured && !showSetup) return 'landing';
  if (!tunnelConfig?.tokenConfigured && showSetup) return 'setup';
  if (tunnelState === 'error') return 'error';
  if (tunnelState === 'starting') return 'connecting';
  if (tunnelState === 'connected') return 'connected';
  return 'ready';
}
```

## State Ownership

The shell retains these state variables:
- `state: TunnelState` ('off' | 'starting' | 'connected' | 'stopping' | 'error')
- `showSetup: boolean` (tracks navigation to setup from landing)
- `error: string | null`
- `url: string | null`
- `domain: string`
- `passcodeEnabled: boolean`
- `passcodeInput: string`
- `latencyMs: number | null`
- All existing `useEffect` hooks (server sync, toast notifications, stuck state recovery, latency measurement)
- All handler functions: `handleToggle`, `handleSaveToken`, `handleSaveDomain`, `handlePasscodeToggle`, `handleSavePasscode`

The shell NO LONGER owns:
- `authToken` state (moves to TunnelSetup)
- `tokenError` state (moves to TunnelSetup)
- `copied`/`copiedSession` state (moves to TunnelConnected via useCopyFeedback)

