Create the connection progress component that replaces the static "Establishing connection..." text with real step-by-step progress indicators driven by elapsed time.

## File to Create

`apps/client/src/layers/features/settings/ui/TunnelConnecting.tsx`

```typescript
import { Loader2, Check } from 'lucide-react';

interface TunnelConnectingProps {
  /** Elapsed time in ms since toggle was flipped — drives step progression. */
  elapsedMs: number;
}

const STEPS = [
  { label: 'Authenticating with ngrok...', appearsAt: 0, completesAt: 1500 },
  { label: 'Establishing secure tunnel...', appearsAt: 500, completesAt: 3000 },
  { label: 'Configuring endpoint...', appearsAt: 1500, completesAt: Infinity },
] as const;

type StepStatus = 'pending' | 'active' | 'completed';

function getStepStatus(step: typeof STEPS[number], elapsedMs: number): StepStatus {
  if (elapsedMs < step.appearsAt) return 'pending';
  if (elapsedMs >= step.completesAt) return 'completed';
  return 'active';
}

/** Connection progress steps during ngrok startup. */
export function TunnelConnecting({ elapsedMs }: TunnelConnectingProps) {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50/50 p-3 dark:border-amber-800 dark:bg-amber-950/30">
      <ul className="space-y-2">
        {STEPS.map((step) => {
          const status = getStepStatus(step, elapsedMs);
          if (status === 'pending') return null;
          return (
            <li key={step.label} className="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
              {status === 'active' && (
                <Loader2 className="size-3.5 animate-spin text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400" />
              )}
              {status === 'completed' && (
                <Check className="size-3.5 text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" />
              )}
              <span className={status === 'completed' ? 'text-muted-foreground' : ''}>
                {step.label}
              </span>
            </li>
          );
        })}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
}
```

Approximate line count: ~70 lines.

## Step Progression Logic

The step progression is time-based (not event-based) since the ngrok SDK does not expose granular connection events through the transport layer:

| Step | Label                         | Appears at | Completes at |
| ---- | ----------------------------- | ---------- | ------------ |
| 1    | Authenticating with ngrok...  | 0ms        | 1500ms       |
| 2    | Establishing secure tunnel... | 500ms      | 3000ms       |
| 3    | Configuring endpoint...       | 1500ms     | on connect   |

Step 3 never auto-completes (`completesAt: Infinity`) — it stays in 'active' status until the parent component transitions away from the connecting state when `transport.startTunnel()` resolves.

## Step Indicator Behavior

- **Pending**: Not rendered (null return)
- **Active**: Spinner icon (`Loader2` with `animate-spin`) + normal text
- **Completed**: Checkmark icon (`Check` in green) + muted text

The amber border and background match the transitional (in-progress) state color used by the status dot in the header.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] At 0ms elapsed: step 1 shows with spinner, steps 2-3 hidden
- [ ] At 500ms: step 1 spinning, step 2 appears with spinner
- [ ] At 1500ms: step 1 shows checkmark (completed), step 2 spinning, step 3 appears with spinner
- [ ] At 3000ms: steps 1-2 completed with checkmarks, step 3 spinning
- [ ] Step 3 never auto-completes (stays active until parent unmounts)
- [ ] Completed steps show muted text color
- [ ] Active steps show spinner icon (`animate-spin`)
- [ ] Card has amber border/background for transitional state
- [ ] No TypeScript errors

