## Reduced Motion Verification

The codebase uses `<MotionConfig reducedMotion="user">` in `App.tsx` which globally handles `prefers-reduced-motion`. This means:
- All `motion/react` animations (motion.div, AnimatePresence, etc.) automatically collapse to instant opacity transitions
- No per-component `useReducedMotion()` calls are needed
- CSS animations (`animate-pulse`, `animate-spin`) need the existing `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` override in the global stylesheet

